  - **Drive real behavior through the public API.** Exercise enough of the
    library's reachable surface that the test fails when metadata is wrong or
    missing. Do not reach for reflection directly unless the public API genuinely
    requires it, and keep tests outside the library's own packages — a test must
    not live in a library package just to touch package-private or internal code.
  - **Test supported behavior, not bugs.** Target behavior the library actually
    supports. Never make an uncovered dynamic-access call site "covered" by
    asserting a known bug, regression, or version-specific failure; exception
    assertions are acceptable only for documented, supported negative-path APIs.
  - **Stay version-agnostic.** Do not pin to a specific library version or hardcode
    the artifact version in inputs or assertions. Scaffold-only tests that do not
    actually exercise the library are not acceptable.
  - **Don't fake the library.** No source stubs, fake replacements, or shadow
    classes for library or dependency types in their real packages. If a needed API
    is missing from the test classpath, add the correct test dependency or leave
    the call site unreached with an explanation — never paper over it.
  - **Run under Native Image by default.** Tests execute on `native-image`, not
    only the JVM; do not disable native execution with `@DisabledInNativeImage`,
    `assumeFalse(...)`, `isNativeImageRuntime()`, or equivalent guards. When a test
    genuinely needs open-ended dynamic class loading that Native Image cannot
    support, prove it fails for the right reason — catch `Error` and verify it with
    `NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(e)` — rather than skipping it.
  - **Be deterministic, isolated, and bounded.** No network except against a
    declared, pre-pulled `allowed-docker-image` with networking disabled, and
    per-coordinate runs must not depend on or affect other coordinates
    (§FS-repository-functional-spec.6). Each individual test completes in under
    60 seconds, using bounded waits and closing every client, server, and executor
    it opens.
  - **Keep test code original.** Do not copy upstream or other third-party test
    sources into this repository. Upstream tests may be used only as behavioral
    examples, and documentation only as API guidance. Review policy details live
    in [REVIEWING.md](REVIEWING.md).
  
  ## 3. How the suite is exercised
  
  The harness compiles and runs each coordinate's project through the
  `compileTestJava` → `javaTest` → `nativeTestCompile` → `nativeTest` lanes
  (§TCK-test-harness.3), and CI runs the same lanes across the `ci.json` JDK/OS
  matrix and native-image modes (§CI-repository-ci). A version is recorded as
  supported only after it passes on every required environment, and dynamic-access
  coverage between consecutive versions must not regress
  (§FS-repository-functional-spec.5.2, §GOAL-protect-shipped-metadata). New test
  projects are created from the scaffold templates by the authoring tasks
  (§TCK-test-harness.5), by a human or by Forge (§forge/FS-forge-functional-spec).
[recv] {"type": "message_start", "message": {"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_SRClW3SNqGunxWjRvGXCyYYN|fc_08d4a494233929b9016a26983ad2448195a5ab5a3bdb405fd2", "toolName": "read", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "\n- **Drive real behavior through the public API.** Exercise enough of the\n  library's reachable surface that the test fails when metadata is wrong or\n  missing. Do not reach for reflection directly unless the public API genuinely\n  requires it, and keep tests outside the library's own packages — a test must\n  not live in a library package just to touch package-private or internal code.\n- **Test supported behavior, not bugs.** Target behavior the library actually\n  supports. Never make an uncovered dynamic-access call site \"covered\" by\n  asserting a known bug, regression, or version-specific failure; exception\n  assertions are acceptable only for documented, supported negative-path APIs.\n- **Stay version-agnostic.** Do not pin to a specific library version or hardcode\n  the artifact version in inputs or assertions. Scaffold-only tests that do not\n  actually exercise the library are not acceptable.\n- **Don't fake the library.** No source stubs, fake replacements, or shadow\n  classes for library or dependency types in their real packages. If a needed API\n  is missing from the test classpath, add the correct test dependency or leave\n  the call site unreached with an explanation — never paper over it.\n- **Run under Native Image by default.** Tests execute on `native-image`, not\n  only the JVM; do not disable native execution with `@DisabledInNativeImage`,\n  `assumeFalse(...)`, `isNativeImageRuntime()`, or equivalent guards. When a test\n  genuinely needs open-ended dynamic class loading that Native Image cannot\n  support, prove it fails for the right reason — catch `Error` and verify it with\n  `NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(e)` — rather than skipping it.\n- **Be deterministic, isolated, and bounded.** No network except against a\n  declared, pre-pulled `allowed-docker-image` with networking disabled, and\n  per-coordinate runs must not depend on or affect other coordinates\n  (§FS-repository-functional-spec.6). Each individual test completes in under\n  60 seconds, using bounded waits and closing every client, server, and executor\n  it opens.\n- **Keep test code original.** Do not copy upstream or other third-party test\n  sources into this repository. Upstream tests may be used only as behavioral\n  examples, and documentation only as API guidance. Review policy details live\n  in [REVIEWING.md](REVIEWING.md).\n\n## 3. How the suite is exercised\n\nThe harness compiles and runs each coordinate's project through the\n`compileTestJava` → `javaTest` → `nativeTestCompile` → `nativeTest` lanes\n(§TCK-test-harness.3), and CI runs the same lanes across the `ci.json` JDK/OS\nmatrix and native-image modes (§CI-repository-ci). A version is recorded as\nsupported only after it passes on every required environment, and dynamic-access\ncoverage between consecutive versions must not regress\n(§FS-repository-functional-spec.5.2, §GOAL-protect-shipped-metadata). New test\nprojects are created from the scaffold templates by the authoring tasks\n(§TCK-test-harness.5), by a human or by Forge (§forge/FS-forge-functional-spec).\n"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1780914235129}}
